CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1953, pg. 23, reads: "LATEST "FIND" - Pictured is little 10-year-old George Benson, guitarist and singer, and his manager, restaurant owner, Harry Tepper. Tepper discovered the youth singing on Hill District street corner for pennies and got him signed to a recording contract."
TitMainTitle: Young George Benson holding guitar, seated next to his manager Harry Tepper, in front of seascape background, in Harris Studio
